[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 0.9"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

The following security holes affect Tails 0.9.

We **strongly** urge you to [[upgrade to Tails 0.10|news/version_0.10]]
as soon as possible in case you are still using an older version.

Details
=======

These are Debian security announces; details can be found on the
[Debian security page](http://security.debian.org/):

  - jasper ([DSA-2371](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2371))
  - libsoup2.4 ([DSA-2369](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2369))
  - xorg ([DSA-2364](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2364))
  - tor ([DSA-2363](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2363))
  - openjdk-6 ([DSA-2358](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2358))
  - evince ([DSA-2357](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2357))
  - cups ([DSA-2354](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2354))
  - freetype ([DSA-2350](http://www.debian.org/security/2011/dsa-2350))
